column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Ice off 4/28/93- perfect weather today- loons chasing for mate.  Water level: up- due to recent rains
Fresh rains diluted fertile waters and diminished algae growth
Overcast.  Water level: up- springs must be working
Perfect day- little wind- no one else on lake.
Lake is most clear than in last 2 years- springs must be active.
Oak pollen around shore.  Water level: Up 8-10"
Partly cloudy. No thermocline. Took Van Dorn and 2 integrated sampler water samples.
Clear- sunny- calm- floating and suspended particles (pollen )- no boats. Jen and Molly Stewart helped.
Sunny- light breeze- 2 loons- 1 jet ski. Jen and Molly Stewart helped.
Sunny- calm- 2 loons- lots of power boat activity earlier. Molly Stewart and Marie Milanowski helped.
Partly sunny- light wind- no boats.
Partly cloudy- light wind- 3 power boats- 2 fishing boats- 2 sailboats. Jen and Molly Stewart helped.
Sunny- windy- 2 power boats- sailboats and kayaks out at girl's camp. Molly Stewart helped.
30% clouds- windy- 2 power boats- 2 jet skis.
Clear- light breeze- 2 power boats- 1 jet ski.
20% clouds- light winds- 3 power boats- 1 jet ski.
30% clouds- windy- 3 power boats- 1 jet ski.
Hazy sun- 3 fishing boats.Jen and Molly Stewart helped.
5% clouds- light breeze-2 fishing boats- 1 loon- 1 bald eagle- slight brownish/yellow color water- small- suspended green particles.
Bruce- Jen- and Molly. 100% overcast- 3-inch waves- 2 loons- 1 fishing boat.
Jen- Bruce- and Molly.  5% overcast- just short of whitecaps- 2 loons.
Bruce and Viv.  100% overcast- light breeze- 2 eagles- 2 loons- 2 fishing boats.
Hazy sun- just short of whitecaps- small suspended particles.  Bruce.
Bruce and Molly.  20% overcast- light breeze- 2 loons- 2 eagles- suspended particles (size of salt grains).
Bruce- Molly- Jen.  10% overcast (cirrus)- calm- loon- eagle- suspended particles ( salt grain sized and smaller- whitish in color)- 5 fishing boats- 2 kayaks.
Bruce.  10% overcast (cumulus)- light breeze- loon- eagle- fishing boat- small whitish suspended particles.
Bruce.  Clear- light breeze- 2 eagles- 4 skiers/tubers- 3 fisherman- wavy due to boat activity.
Bruce and Molly.  25% overcast(cumulus)- light breeze- 2 eagles- 2 fishing boats.
Bruce- Randy Zogbaum- and Jackson.  50% overcast- light breeze- 3 skiers/tubers.
Bruce- Jen- and Molly.  25% cirrus- light breeze- 1 fishing boat.
2 loons feeding. Molly caught a 16 inch small mouth bass.  Bruce and Molly Stewart. Bruce and Molly Stewart.
Clear and warm. Light breeze- 3 loons. Bruce and Molly Stewart.
Sunny. Light breeze. 2 loons- 1 eagle. Deepest reading that I have recorded.
Sunny. Light breeze- 2 loons- 1 eagle and 2 waterskiers
Beautiful day.  5" of rain in last 2 weeks.
beautiful day- 6+" of rain in last 3 days.
Suspended particles in murky water- brown cast. Super high.
beautiful calm day- lake level down 5" in last month
sunny calm day.  water 76 degrees- limited recent rain-  lake level down 8" from summer peak.
high runoff from record winter snow- lake level high- surface temp 48 degrees
high runoff from record winter snow- water temp 48 at surface- lake level high
very wet + cold spring- water temp 58 at surface- lake level high
not much rain last 3 weeks but lake level still high- water temp 69 at surface- been cold spring
very dry the last month- water level -4.5" since dock-in- water temp 78 at surface- lots of boat traffic over 7/4 week.
continues to be a very dry summer- water level -7" since dock-in- water temp 76 at surface
2-3" of rain in last week- water temp 74 at surface- water level -6" since dock-in
recent above normal rain- water temp 65 at surface- water level -5" since dock-in
rainy Aug + Sept- water temp 66 at surface- water level -3" since dock-in
ice off 4/18- water temp 50 at surface- lake level high from snow melt + rain
water temp 59 at surface- not much rain last 3 weeks- level -1" since dock in
water temp 72 at surface- 3"+ rain in last 10 days- lake level -2" since dock in
Partly sunny. 1 speed boat. 1 adult bald eagle
water temp 81 at surface- little rain + high air temps in last 10 days- lake level -3" since dock-in
water temp 75 at surface- lots of rain and high boat traffic seem to be affecting clarity
water temp 73 at surface- little rain the last couple weeks so lake level has dropped about 4"
water temp 62 at surface- water level -3" since putting dock in in spring.
